Post description: Greetings, I am copying existing html into a Moodle book chapter. This doc has some complex tables, and I'd like to grab the . css from my original html (from an EPUB.)  I've updated mod/books/styles.css but my new styles aren't displaying. 
```text

```
 All of the styles from the original moodle mod/books/styles.css seem to have 
```text
.path-mod-book .navbottom
```
 I've added to the styles.css with styles like this one, below. Do I need some kind of ".path-mod-book" prefix? Many thanks! 
```text
  table.border-k td{
    margin-top:1em;
    margin-bottom:1em;
    margin-left:em;
    margin-right:0em;
    padding: 0.5em;
